events.name: Boston Celtics at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum and Jaylen Brown hit back-to-back 3-pointers less than two minutes into their matchup with New Orleans, foreshadowing a long, frustrating night for the Pelicans as they tried to defend the Celtics' top two scorers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Brown lead Celtics over Pelicans, 107-97

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 30 points and 12 assists and the Dallas Mavericks spoiled former coach Rick Carlisle’s return with Indiana, routing the Pacers 132-105 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Kleber lead Mavericks past Carlisle, Pacers 132-105

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid put his versatility on display and the 76ers on his back.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 36 points, leads 76ers over Kings

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet hit two 3-pointers in the third overtime and the Toronto Raptors outlasted the Miami Heat 124-120 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fred VanVleet, Raptors outlast Heat in 124-120 in triple-OT

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 34 points, his sixth straight game of at least 30 points, and the Memphis Grizzlies built an early lead in a 115-95 victory over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ja Morant scores 34 points, Grizzlies beat Wizards 115-95

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson is right back to knocking down timely shots that help decide games and playing stingy defense on the other end.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry, Warriors beat Kyrie Irving, Nets 110-106
